radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: Computed tomography (CT) of the thorax, abdomen, and pelvis
radiographic_examinations.findings: CT revealed a single liver that spanned the shared abdominal cavity, each twin had one dominant kidney with a ureter draining into a shared bladder, and a smaller dysplastic kidney. Major shared arterial blood supply was observed with a dilated superior mesenteric artery communicating with the abdominal aorta.
Chest radiograph revealed bibasilar air-space opacities that were more prominent on the left side than on the right side.
Echocardiography revealed that Twin A had complex congenital heart disease, and Twin B had dextrocardia with otherwise normal cardiac anatomy.
